GirlSpace Community Guidelines

Last updated: 13 November 2025

GirlSpace is a safe, girls-only community designed to offer emotional support, friendship, and meaningful conversations. To maintain a secure and positive environment, all users must follow these Community Guidelines.

By using the GirlSpace app, you agree to comply with these rules. Violations may result in warnings, temporary suspension, or permanent removal from the platform.

1. Who Can Use GirlSpace

GirlSpace is strictly for:

Women and girls

Age 18 and above

Genuine identities only (no impersonation)

We reserve the right to verify accounts or request additional verification for safety reasons.

2. Content Allowed

You may:

Chat respectfully with others

Share supportive messages

Post positive content related to friendship, lifestyle, wellness, study, career, hobbies

Share photos that are safe, decent, and non-abusive

Participate in groups (premium feature)

3. Content NOT Allowed (Strictly Prohibited)

The following content is not allowed under any circumstances:

A. Harassment & Abuse

Bullying

Insults, name-calling

Threats or intimidation

Targeted harassment or shaming

B. Sexual or Adult Content

Nudity

Pornographic material

Sexually suggestive messages/images

Requests for explicit content

C. Illegal or Harmful Activities

Drugs, weapons, violence

Human trafficking

Self-harm encouragement

Fraud, scams, fake profiles

D. Hate Speech

Racism

Sexism

Religious hate

Any harmful, discriminatory language

E. Impersonation / Fake Identity

Pretending to be someone you are not

Using someone else’s photos

Using fake names or misleading profiles

F. SPAM & Scams

Sending mass messages

Advertising products/services

MLM / crypto promotions

Phishing or misleading links

4. Media Sharing Rules

When sending images, audio, or video:

No explicit or inappropriate content

No abusive or violent content

No copyrighted media unless you own the rights

No sharing private info of others without permission

All media is automatically checked using AI-based content moderation filters to protect users.

5. Reporting & Moderation

Users can report:

Messages

Profiles

Behaviors

Content

GirlSpace has:

Automated AI moderation

Human moderators for escalated cases

Temporary bans for first violations

Permanent account deletion for repeated or severe violations

6. Consequences of Violations

Depending on severity, the following actions may occur:

Warning message

Temporary restriction from messaging

Removal from groups

Removal of content

Account suspension

Permanent ban

Legal reporting (only in cases of serious threats or illegal activity)

7. Safety Tips

Do not share personal information (address, financial details, OTPs)

Avoid meeting strangers without verifying their identity

Block any suspicious user immediately

Use the Report button whenever you feel unsafe

8. Contact & Support

If you believe someone is violating these rules or you feel unsafe, contact us:

